---
layout: page
slug: about-us
---

%section#testimonials
  %h1.sr-only Testimonials
  .container
    #testimonials.row
      #testimonials-slideshow.col-sm-10
        - data.testimonials.each do |i, testimonial|
          = partial "partials/index/testimonial", locals: { testimonial: testimonial }

      #testimonials-action.col-sm-2
        %p Looking to build a Web or mobile app?
        = link_to "Get in touch", "/contact/", class: "btn btn-default"

%section#services
  %h1.sr-only Our Services
  .container
    .row
      .col-sm-6
        :kramdown
          We work closely with businesses in Australia and the UK to improve customer experience, increase sales, and simplify and automate their work with great software.

        %ul.row
          %li.service-design.col-sm-3.col-xs-6
            = icon("pencil", modify: "fluid")
            Design
          %li.service-web.col-sm-3.col-xs-6
            = icon("monitor", modify: "fluid")
            Web Apps
          %li.service-mobile.col-sm-3.col-xs-6
            = icon("tablet", modify: "fluid")
            Mobile Apps
          %li.service-training.col-sm-3.col-xs-6
            = icon("medal", modify: "fluid")
            Training

        = link_to "View case studies and more about our services", "/services/", class: "btn btn-default"

      .col-sm-6
        .row
          = image_tag "/images/devices.png", width:"618", height:"328", class: "img-responsive"

%section#about
  %h1.sr-only About Us
  .container
    .row
      #team.col-sm-6
        %h2 The Team
        %ul.row
          - ["robert", "dominic", "sam"].each do |name|
            = partial "partials/index/team_member", locals: { username: name, member: data.team.send(name) }

      #history.col-sm-6
        %h2 About Terracoding
        :kramdown
          Terracoding is based in Sheffield and Manchester, UK. Weâ€™ve been working with clients internationally since 2011, advising on development strategy, designing interfaces users enjoy and writing fast, dependable code.

          We value testing and like to work in an #{define("Agile")} way, iterating on an idea with the client to produce the best solution.

%section#partners
  .container
    %h1 Clients &amp; Partners
    %ul#partner-logos
      - data.partners.each do |name, url|
        %li
          = link_to url do
            = image_tag "/images/partners/#{slugify(name)}.png", alt: name
